Communities are being urged to comply with lockdown regulations and act responsibly to contain COVID-19. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Communities are being urged to comply with lockdown regulations and act responsibly to contain COVID-19. But is this possible in densely populated areas? READ: SA's vulnerable queue to access grants early amid lockdown Most residents share small living quarters and have to share taps and toilets. Alexandra and Khayelitsha are two of the most congested townships in the country and there have already been confirmed cases in those areas. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.